summary:
The Security Council,
Recalling all its previous resolutions on Western Sahara, and reaffirming resolution 1495 (2003) of 31 July 2003,
Decides to extend the mandate of MINURSO until 31 January 2004; 
Requests the Secretary-General to report on the situation before the end of the present mandate; 
Decides to remain seized of the matter.
